extends layout.pug

block content
  section.hero
    .hero-inner
      p.brand-lockup Arbiter
      h1.hero-title The agent that runs anywhere.
      p.hero-lede One small binary for laptops, servers, CI, and edge — supervised agents with durable memory and a live event stream.
      .install-callout(aria-label="Install command")
        span Install
        code= installCommand
        button.button(
          type="button"
          data-copy-install=installCommand
        ) Copy

  section#product.product-stage.reveal
    .product-stage-inner
      p.eyebrow Terminal interface
      h2 Multi-pane sessions. Inline diffs. Live streams.
      .product-frame
        img(
          src="/assets/terminal.jpg"
          alt="Arbiter terminal interface with sessions and inline diff rendering"
          width="1600"
          height="1000"
        )
        .product-meta
          span arbiter — interactive TUI
          span same runtime as CLI + HTTP API

  section#platform.section.reveal
    .section-inner
      p.eyebrow Platform
      h2 Route. Supervise. Replay.
      p.section-lede Map real events to the right agent, constrain tools with advisor gates, and keep every stream reconnectable.
      .feature-rail
        article.feature
          h3 Route
          p Prompts, webhooks, incidents, schedules, and hardware events land on agents with explicit constitutions.
        article.feature
          h3 Supervise
          p Tool access is an allowlist. Advisor gates review consequential turns before work leaves the runtime.
        article.feature
          h3 Replay
          p Persist request streams so clients can reconnect, audit, or tail in-flight work without losing context.

  section#workflow.section.section-band.reveal
    .section-inner.split-section
      div
        p.eyebrow How it works
        h2 One event stream from request to result.
        p.section-lede Routing, delegation, tool calls, memory reads, advisor gates, and token use stay visible as structured events.
      .steps
        .step
          span 01
          strong Receive
          p Accept a prompt, CLI send, HTTP request, webhook, schedule, or device event.
        .step
          span 02
          strong Route
          p Match the work to an agent constitution with explicit tools, memory, and event patterns.
        .step
          span 03
          strong Act
          p Execute writ commands inline while advisor gates review consequential decisions.
        .step
          span 04
          strong Observe
          p Stream and persist every event so clients can reconnect, inspect, and audit outcomes.

  section#surfaces.section.reveal
    .section-inner
      p.eyebrow Surfaces
      h2 Same runtime. Optional interfaces.
      p.section-lede Drive agents from the TUI, one-shot CLI, HTTP API, or Agent2Agent clients without changing the binary underneath.
      .feature-rail
        article.feature
          h3 Operators
          p Route production incidents, scheduled checks, queue messages, and service webhooks into supervised runs.
        article.feature
          h3 Developers
          p Script one-shots, embed the API, or keep a multi-pane TUI open on the machine that owns the work.
        article.feature
          h3 Devices
          p Let sensors and edge machines emit structured events while Arbiter handles routing, memory, and action.

  section#themes.section.section-band.reveal
    .section-inner
      p.eyebrow Themeable
      h2 No color compiled into the binary.
      p.section-lede The TUI reads a JSON theme at startup. Presets ship in-tree; save your own look without rebuilding.
      .themes-panel
        img(
          src="/assets/themes.jpg"
          alt="Arbiter TUI theme gallery across multiple color palettes"
          width="1600"
          height="900"
          loading="lazy"
        )

  section#docs.section.reveal
    .section-inner
      p.eyebrow Documentation
      h2 Docs that ship with the code.
      p.section-lede This site ingests repository Markdown directly, so implementation and documentation stay on the same path.
      .flow
        a.flow-row(href=gettingStartedHref)
          code getting-started
          span Install locally, configure providers, and get the first agent reply.
        a.flow-row(href=philosophyHref)
          code philosophy
          span The design themes behind Arbiter's runtime, memory, and supervision model.
        a.flow-row(href=apiHref)
          code api
          span HTTP, SSE, tenants, requests, conversations, schedules, agents, and A2A endpoints.
